<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="798" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Count
                                    <persName type="to">Cassini</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-09-15"><hi rend="italic">September 15,
                                    1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The admiral at San Francisco advises me this morning that the captain of
                            the <hi rend="italic">Lena</hi> writes him that the ship being
                            unseaworthy must disarm, and asks to be allowed to make needed repairs.
                            When the President shall have approved the conditions necessary to
                            insure the neutralization of the <hi rend="italic">Lena</hi> and her
                            officers and crew until the end of the war, and to permit necessary
                            repairs, the admiral will be instructed to cause the disarmament to be
                            effected, whereupon I shall have pleasure in advising you further.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of State.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>